// ---- 05:263 second half. Replaces an unverifiable `utmctl version` observation (which sends an Apple
// Event and launches UTM.app -- a side effect the ledger's verifier must not have) with a pure file read.
{"id": "utm-app-version-is-4-7-5", "kind": "file-contains", "file": "specs/macos-ci/05-utm-automation.md", "target": "/Applications/UTM.app/Contents/Info.plist", "expect": "<string>4.7.5</string>", "claim": "UTM.app on this host is 4.7.5, the version 05 s4.1 reports from `utmctl version`. Read from the bundle's XML Info.plist, which costs nothing and mutates nothing -- whereas `utmctl version` dispatches an Apple Event and LAUNCHES UTM.app if it is not running. Same fact, no side effect. Host-specific by design: when UTM updates, this claim fails and 05 must be re-read."}

