// Sharpens 08 s'the run' (and 10's ADR): tart's exec is ALSO guest-agent-gated -- but the agent SHIPS in
// Cirrus Labs images, whereas an Apple-backend macOS guest under UTM has no agent at all (G18).
{"id": "xaudit-08-tart-exec-requires-guest-agent", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/08-dotfiles-test-harness.md", "argv": ["tart", "exec", "--help"], "expect": "Requires Tart Guest Agent running in a guest VM", "claim": "`tart exec` needs the Tart Guest Agent (its help adds: all non-vanilla Cirrus Labs images already have it). So the tart-vs-UTM asymmetry is NOT `tart has exec, UTM does not` -- BOTH exec paths are agent-gated. The real asymmetry: tart's agent is prebuilt into the images, and `tart ip`'s DEFAULT dhcp resolver needs no agent at all, whereas utmctl's ip-address has only the agent path (utmctl-exec-needs-qemu-guest-agent). 08 is right to use ssh, but for this reason, not the one it gives."}

